14/*
15 * The X86 architecture is peculiar with regards to floating point comparisons.
16 * When testing if a FP value is a particular constant, compilers first have
17 * to test for whether or not the argument is NaN, thus incurring the
18 * cost of two jumps. One for the NaN, and then the second for some form of
19 * equality (==, <, >, ...).
20 *
21 * Given the following function as an example:
22 * double f(x)
23 * {
24 * if (0.0 == x)
25 * return (x);
26 * return (x*x);
27 * }
28 *
29 * We have the following generated code:
30 * .p2align 4,,15
31 * .globl f
32 * .type f, @function
33 * f:
34 * .LFB0:
35 * .cfi_startproc
36 * ucomisd .LC0(%rip), %xmm0 <=== Compare x and constant 0.0
37 * movapd %xmm0, %xmm1
38 * jp .L5 <======== If x is NaN, return x*x
39 * je .L2 <======== If 0.0 == x, return x (%xmm1)
40 * .L5:
41 * movapd %xmm1, %xmm0
42 * mulsd %xmm1, %xmm0
43 * .L2:
44 * rep ret
45 * .cfi_endproc
46 * .LFE0:
47 * .size f, .-f
48 * .section .rodata.cst8,"aM",@progbits,8
49 * .align 8
50 * .LC0:
51 * .long 0
52 * .long 0
53 *
54 *
55 * As an optimization in the scalar single and double precision EXP()
56 * functions, we test to see if the argument is zero and if so short circuit
57 * the logic and immediately return 1.0.
58 *
59 * But the cost of two jump tests is expensive. We instead compare the
60 * input argument as an integer looking for +- zero thus only having
61 * a single jump in the instruction sequence.
62 *
63 * For X8664 platforms the macros _ISFZEROPT0(float) and _ISDZEROPT0(double)
64 * do the appropriate recasting of the arguments to test against integer
65 * 0. Other platforms, the floating point test against 0.0 remains.
66 *
67 */
68
69#ifdef LINUX8664
70#define _ISFZEROPT0(_x) (0 == (*(int32_t *)&(_x)) << 1)
71#define _ISDZEROPT0(_x) (0 == (*(int64_t *)&(_x)) << 1)
72#else
73#define _ISFZEROPT0(_x) (0.0 == (_x))
74#define _ISDZEROPT0(_x) (0.0 == (_x))
75#endif

3767/*
3768 * __{frp}d_powi_2 and __{frp}d_powi_2m should technically be defined as:
3769 * __{frp}d_powi_2(vrd2_t x, vis4_t iy)
3770 * __{frp}d_powi_2m(vrd2_t x, vis4_t iy, vid2_t mask)
3771 *
3772 * But the POWER architectures needs the 32-bit integer vectors to
3773 * be the full 128-bits of a vector register.
3774 */
3775
3776vrd2_t
3777MTH_DISPATCH_FUNC(__fd_powi_2)(vrd2_t x, vis4_t iy)
3778{
3779 vrd2_t (*fptr)(vrd2_t, vis4_t);
3780 _MTH_I_INIT();
3781 _MTH_I_STATS_INC(func_powi,sv_dv2,frp_f);
3782 fptr = (vrd2_t(*)(vrd2_t, vis4_t))MTH_DISPATCH_TBL[func_powi][sv_dv2][frp_f];
3783 return(fptr(x, iy));
3784}
